Toyota South Africa Sells $113 Million Worth of Bonds, Standard Bank Says

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-07-28T12:49:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/toyota-s-africa-sells-760-million-rand-of-bonds-standard-says.html
Toyota Motor Corp. (7203) â€™s South African
unit raised 760 million rand selling four-year floating-rate
bonds and five-year fixed-rate notes, said  Standard Bank  Group
Ltd., which helped arrange the sale.  The four-year bonds were issued at a rate of 85 basis
points above the three-month Johannesburg Interbank Acceptance
Rate, Johannesburg-based Standard Bank said in an e-mailed
statement today. The five-year notes were issued at a spread of
130 basis points over the R157 government bond, resulting in a
coupon of 8.7 percent, it said.  The offer attracted bids worth 1.7 billion rand, Standard
Bank said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
